summary: This document is a preparation memo for trial testimony, summarizing clarifications from an interview with a law enforcement officer (IN). It details the seizure of specific evidence (message pads and a sex toy) from 358 El Brillo Way on October 20, 2005, and the chain of custody for that evidence.

events.title: Evidence Seizure at 358 El Brillo Way
events.description: Law enforcement officer IN seized evidence, including message pads and a 'twin torpedoes' sex toy, from the residence at 358 El Brillo Way.

events.title: Trial Testimony Preparation Interview
events.description: An interview was conducted via VTC with officer IN to prepare for upcoming trial testimony, clarifying details about the 2005 evidence seizure.

keyFacts: Specific evidence seized from 358 El Brillo Way on October 20, 2005, included message pads and a 'twin torpedoes' sex toy.
Photographs of the seized items are confirmed as fair and accurate depictions of the scene as it appeared on the seizure date.
All evidence from the seizure was turned over to a supervised evidence collection team and then transported to the Palm Beach Police Department (PBPD).
The document is a preparation memo for trial testimony, indicating an active legal proceeding related to the Epstein case as of July 2021.
The document is subject to a protective order covering specific paragraphs (7, 8, 9, 10, 15, and 17).
